00:55:49,779 --> 00:55:54,350
<i>( OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING )</i>

718
00:56:17,841 --> 00:56:20,242
<i>( WOMAN SPEAKING FRENCH )</i>

719
00:56:27,751 --> 00:56:32,221
<i>( EERIE MUSIC FADES UP )</i>

720
00:56:32,223 --> 00:56:33,922
John...

721
00:56:33,924 --> 00:56:35,824
John, Why don't you help me?

722
00:56:35,826 --> 00:56:38,193
Why don't you wanna help me?

723
00:56:38,195 --> 00:56:39,795
Mom!

724
00:56:39,797 --> 00:56:41,430
( GIRLS SCREAMING )

725
00:56:41,432 --> 00:56:47,936
ANNA (O.S.): This old man,
he played three.

726
00:56:47,938 --> 00:56:51,840
He played
knick-knack on my knee.

727
00:56:51,842 --> 00:56:53,842
With a knick-knack
paddy whack...

728
00:56:53,844 --> 00:56:56,311
give a dog a bone, this old--

729
00:56:56,313 --> 00:56:58,747
Who's there?

730
00:57:03,586 --> 00:57:07,189
<i>( EERIE MUSIC FADES UP )</i>

731
00:57:21,304 --> 00:57:22,438
Anna?

732
00:57:26,042 --> 00:57:27,376
Anna!

733
00:57:31,281 --> 00:57:34,583
( PHONE RINGING )

734
00:57:34,585 --> 00:57:36,185
Hello?

735
00:57:36,187 --> 00:57:38,687
( CALLER HANGS UP )

736
00:57:38,689 --> 00:57:41,490
( DRAMATIC MUSIC FADES UP )

737
00:58:17,393 --> 00:58:20,262
( RUSTLING )

738
00:58:25,635 --> 00:58:28,237
( TWIGS SNAPPING )

739
00:58:32,141 --> 00:58:35,444
Hey!

740
00:58:35,446 --> 00:58:36,778
Wait!

741
00:58:48,525 --> 00:58:50,826
Wait!

742
00:59:13,850 --> 00:59:15,517
Is there somewhere I
can freshen up?

743
00:59:15,519 --> 00:59:18,654
There's a bathroom just down
that corridor on your left.

744
00:59:18,656 --> 00:59:20,255
Oh, thank you.

745
00:59:24,827 --> 00:59:29,565
( CLOCK CHIMING )

746
00:59:40,677 --> 00:59:44,146
( CHIMING CONTINUES )

747
01:00:07,570 --> 01:00:10,138
( SOFT MUSIC FADES UP )

748
01:01:02,725 --> 01:01:07,062
What are you doing in here?

749
01:01:07,064 --> 01:01:09,665
Maybe I'm looking for the
guy from last night.

750
01:01:12,368 --> 01:01:17,739
You know, Mr. Greene, it really
isn't necessary to
have me followed.

751
01:01:17,741 --> 01:01:21,009
I had you extensively looked
into before you were hired.

752
01:01:21,011 --> 01:01:23,612
I don't have anyone
following you now.

753
01:01:23,614 --> 01:01:28,316
And now, if you'd be so kind,
your work in this
house is upstairs.

754
01:01:36,459 --> 01:01:39,528
( SOFT MUSIC PLAYING )

755
01:02:24,674 --> 01:02:26,508
Very nice, Anna.

756
01:02:29,011 --> 01:02:32,180
Not just yet.

757
01:02:50,433 --> 01:02:53,568
( MUSIC FADES UP )

758
01:03:15,258 --> 01:03:18,126
Glad you're back from
zombie land.

759
01:03:18,128 --> 01:03:20,695
You okay, want some water?

760
01:03:25,301 --> 01:03:29,104
Aren't they great? Better than
what you had before.

761
01:03:30,406 --> 01:03:31,940
How did you do that?

762
01:03:31,942 --> 01:03:34,209
I just downloaded it.

763
01:03:34,211 --> 01:03:36,511
No, how did you leave me
alone in the memory?

764
01:03:36,513 --> 01:03:38,713
I don't know.

765
01:03:38,715 --> 01:03:43,185
Suddenly I was back here, and
our hands were separated, but
you were still under.

766
01:03:43,187 --> 01:03:45,620
I wasn't sure what to do.

767
01:03:50,193 --> 01:03:52,727
You looked cute while you
were sleeping.

768
01:04:02,205 --> 01:04:05,574
Anna, do you know what
transference is?

769
01:04:06,642 --> 01:04:08,210
I do.

770
01:04:08,212 --> 01:04:10,312
Then you'll know it's
perfectly natural to--

771
01:04:10,314 --> 01:04:13,982
To what? Have strong feelings
for your therapist?

772
01:04:13,984 --> 01:04:17,085
I just simply said I liked
watching you sleep.

773
01:04:18,554 --> 01:04:21,323
Your teacher was a lot older
than you, he took advantage.

774
01:04:21,325 --> 01:04:25,493
He was encouraging... that
place was so depressing.

775
01:04:25,495 --> 01:04:27,529
What about the photos?

776
01:04:27,531 --> 01:04:31,233
He said they were for art, and
at first they were artistic.

777
01:05:21,851 --> 01:05:25,287
<i>( EERIE MUSIC FADES UP )</i>

778
01:06:05,261 --> 01:06:07,028
You okay? You don't
look too good.

779
01:06:07,030 --> 01:06:09,464
I'm having trouble
staying grounded.

780
01:06:09,466 --> 01:06:12,033
Side-effects from the sessions?
Hallucinations?

781
01:06:12,035 --> 01:06:13,401
Yeah... terrible headaches.

782
01:06:13,403 --> 01:06:15,704
I can't sleep... nightmares.

783
01:06:15,706 --> 01:06:17,339
Plus the guy they've hired
to follow me...

784
01:06:17,341 --> 01:06:19,341
he's... he is everywhere I go.

785
01:06:19,343 --> 01:06:25,046
Maybe events have made this
case far bigger than you were
ready for when you started.

786
01:06:25,048 --> 01:06:27,148
Maybe we should ask
Lundgren to take over.

787
01:06:27,150 --> 01:06:30,352
No! No way, no. I
can handle it.

788
01:06:32,922 --> 01:06:35,724
Did you ever treat Anna
at their house?

789
01:06:35,726 --> 01:06:37,058
No.

790
01:06:37,060 --> 01:06:40,261
Did you ever have reason to
suspect abuse
within the family?

791
01:06:40,263 --> 01:06:41,796
Nothing with the stepfather?

792
01:06:41,798 --> 01:06:45,633
Highly unlikely. I mean, look,
Robert's a prominent guy.

793
01:06:45,635 --> 01:06:48,970
I wouldn't go down that road
based on a hunch.

794
01:06:48,972 --> 01:06:51,806
Tom Ortega told me Anna's
parents set him up for--

795
01:06:51,808 --> 01:06:54,576
You went to see Tom Ortega?

796
01:06:54,578 --> 01:06:57,345
That lowlife took dirty
pictures of Anna.

797
01:06:57,347 --> 01:07:00,515
You should be focusing on the
sessions, not investigating
in the real world.

798
01:07:00,517 --> 01:07:02,283
You need to be objective, John.

799
01:07:02,285 --> 01:07:06,254
There is something going on
there behind the scenes...

800
01:07:06,256 --> 01:07:07,922
I need to find out what it is.

801
01:07:07,924 --> 01:07:11,259
You need to consider that this
job is too big and
too complex...

802
01:07:11,261 --> 01:07:13,661
and that you are becoming too
personally involved.

803
01:07:13,663 --> 01:07:16,664
Whatever it is, I'm gonna
find out the truth.

804
01:07:24,440 --> 01:07:28,410
<i>( DRAMATIC MUSIC FADES UP )</i>

805
01:07:45,461 --> 01:07:47,796
Do you know where
you want to go?

806
01:07:47,798 --> 01:07:52,600
I went through all the photos
and one of them made me
feel something.

807
01:07:52,602 --> 01:07:53,802
Don't tell me.

808
01:07:53,804 --> 01:07:56,271
Don't corrupt the memory,
just go there.

809
01:08:00,709 --> 01:08:04,579
When you're ready,
close your eyes.

810
01:08:06,782 --> 01:08:10,685
Let's begin... now.

811
01:08:15,458 --> 01:08:18,193
My parents brought him to me.
Who?

812
01:08:18,195 --> 01:08:19,861
I don't remember his name.

813
01:08:22,264 --> 01:08:24,833
( CLOCK CHIMES )

814
01:08:29,305 --> 01:08:32,674
This old man, he played three.

815
01:08:32,676 --> 01:08:35,610
He played
knick-knack on my knee.

816
01:08:35,612 --> 01:08:39,981
With a knick-knack paddy whack,
give a dog a bone.

817
01:08:39,983 --> 01:08:44,152
This old man came rolling home.

818
01:08:44,154 --> 01:08:46,688
<i>( OMINOUS MUSIC FADES UP )</i>

819
01:09:00,302 --> 01:09:02,470
( WOOD BLOCKS CLANKING )

820
01:09:06,208 --> 01:09:08,743
What are you doing over there,
Anna?

821
01:09:10,346 --> 01:09:14,349
Why don't you come here...
next to me.

822
01:09:15,885 --> 01:09:18,686
Come here, sweetheart.

823
01:09:29,298 --> 01:09:30,498
Don't be afraid.

824
01:09:30,500 --> 01:09:32,467
( BREATHING HEAVILY )

825
01:09:32,469 --> 01:09:36,437
I won't hurt you.

826
01:09:36,439 --> 01:09:38,673
And coming back... now!

827
01:09:43,712 --> 01:09:45,013
Anna?

828
01:09:45,015 --> 01:09:46,414
( STEPS APPROACHING ) ( DOOR
OPENING, CLOSING )

829
01:09:46,416 --> 01:09:47,749
Anna, can you hear me?

830
01:09:47,751 --> 01:09:48,983
( DOOR OPENS, STEPS
APPROACHING )

831
01:09:48,985 --> 01:09:50,118
You're okay, you fainted.

832
01:09:50,120 --> 01:09:51,386
RALPH (O.S.): What happened?

833
01:09:51,388 --> 01:09:53,821
Can you get some water.
She's okay.

834
01:09:53,823 --> 01:09:56,457
RALPH (O.S.): Yeah, sure.

835
01:10:00,162 --> 01:10:02,096
Take this.

836
01:10:02,098 --> 01:10:04,165
What is it?

837
01:10:04,167 --> 01:10:08,503
It's a bit of one of your mom's
sedatives. It'll
help you sleep.

838
01:10:15,511 --> 01:10:17,812
So, what happens now?

839
01:10:17,814 --> 01:10:22,150
Now... you get better.

840
01:10:27,923 --> 01:10:31,993
( SOFT MUSIC PLAYING )

841
01:10:38,968 --> 01:10:43,605
This is the key to the house my
parents lived in
when I was born.

842
01:10:43,607 --> 01:10:46,507
I always felt safe there.

843
01:10:46,509 --> 01:10:49,344
So many times in my life
people have been unkind.

844
01:10:49,346 --> 01:10:53,214
I can't thank you enough, John.

845
01:10:53,216 --> 01:10:57,151
Will you keep this with
you at all times?

846
01:10:57,153 --> 01:11:00,255
If I know you have it, then at
least I know that there's
someone out there...

847
01:11:00,257 --> 01:11:01,923
who's on my side.

848
01:11:01,925 --> 01:11:05,226
I might not be going to
an institution...

849
01:11:05,228 --> 01:11:08,129
but I still feel trapped.

850
01:11:08,131 --> 01:11:09,697
Sure.

851
01:11:14,069 --> 01:11:18,172
( THUNDER ROLLING )

852
01:11:26,882 --> 01:11:29,651
Hey! Hey!

853
01:11:33,222 --> 01:11:34,622
John? What are you doing here?

854
01:11:34,624 --> 01:11:36,424
You should have called, I've
got dinner guests.

855
01:11:36,426 --> 01:11:38,259
Why Sebastian?

856
01:11:38,261 --> 01:11:40,395
Christ! She was just a child.

857
01:11:40,397 --> 01:11:42,664
What's going on? You've
been drinking?

858
01:11:43,799 --> 01:11:46,634
These were in Anna's memories.

859
01:11:46,636 --> 01:11:48,870
Have you been in my office?

860
01:11:48,872 --> 01:11:52,974
I've seen you with her, in the
library, in one of
the memories.

861
01:11:52,976 --> 01:11:55,343
Oh, I might have been there
once, I forgot!

862
01:11:55,345 --> 01:11:57,245
What's this all about?

863
01:11:57,247 --> 01:12:00,815
You said you never treated her
at the house, but
you were there!

864
01:12:02,418 --> 01:12:05,353
Are you trying to say I did
something to her?

865
01:12:05,355 --> 01:12:07,355
Think this through, John.

866
01:12:07,357 --> 01:12:12,560
Why would I ask you to take on
a case, if I was guilty
of something?

867
01:12:12,562 --> 01:12:14,762
Think about what it is you're
accusing me of...

868
01:12:14,764 --> 01:12:18,700
then, think about who it is
you're accusing.

869
01:12:18,702 --> 01:12:20,702
They wanted to hire
Peter Lundgren.

870
01:12:20,704 --> 01:12:23,838
You brought me in, because I
was down, and I was weak...

871
01:12:23,840 --> 01:12:26,941
and I was easy to manipulate.
Right?

872
01:12:26,943 --> 01:12:30,445
And you wouldn't let me see
that file until you
absolutely had to.

873
01:12:30,447 --> 01:12:33,648
You said they didn't want me to
see it, but you had it
the whole time!

874
01:12:33,650 --> 01:12:35,883
I never told you I didn't
have the file!

875
01:12:35,885 --> 01:12:39,053
I said the family
wanted privacy.

876
01:12:39,055 --> 01:12:41,689
What about the other day? Ah?
You wanted me to drop the case.

877
01:12:41,691 --> 01:12:43,291
I said that because--

878
01:12:43,293 --> 01:12:45,893
Now... I know what you didn't
want me to find out.

879
01:12:45,895 --> 01:12:48,396
I said that because I was
worried about you!

880
01:12:48,398 --> 01:12:51,833
Oh, c'mon, John!

881
01:12:51,835 --> 01:12:54,802
You've been drinking alone.
Having hallucinations for days!

882
01:12:54,804 --> 01:12:57,138
You're ignoring me again,
Uncle Sebastian

883
01:12:57,140 --> 01:12:58,740
Hi, sweetheart.

884
01:12:59,908 --> 01:13:02,577
Sorry. John--

885
01:13:02,579 --> 01:13:07,148
Don't you ever go near Anna
again! You hear me?

886
01:13:10,285 --> 01:13:12,987
John!

887
01:13:12,989 --> 01:13:14,255
John!

888
01:13:17,826 --> 01:13:21,095
JOHN (O.S.): Due to Anna's
early overt sexualization...

889
01:13:21,097 --> 01:13:22,730
she has a need for control...

890
01:13:22,732 --> 01:13:26,334
which manifests itself in a
variety of disorders.

891
01:13:26,336 --> 01:13:28,936
She has... significant
difficulty...

892
01:13:28,938 --> 01:13:33,775
in forming and maintaining
long-term
relationships with others.

893
01:13:33,777 --> 01:13:36,110
Basically, she has developed a
protective shell...

894
01:13:36,112 --> 01:13:37,612
Do you like it? which keeps
out the pain...

895
01:13:37,614 --> 01:13:41,282
and keeps out everything else.
It's great.

896
01:13:41,284 --> 01:13:44,886
She interacts with the world in
a completely different way
than the way we do.

897
01:13:44,888 --> 01:13:48,122
Locking her up is the worst
possible thing you could do.

898
01:13:53,996 --> 01:13:57,999
Thank you so much, Mr.
Washington.

899
01:13:58,001 --> 01:14:00,034
Good luck.

900
01:14:05,307 --> 01:14:08,976
<i>( DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING )</i>

901
01:14:22,191 --> 01:14:24,192
( SHOWER RUNNING )

902
01:14:34,603 --> 01:14:37,839
( WOMAN HUMMING "THIS OLD MAN"
)

903
01:14:41,710 --> 01:14:45,246
<i>( DRAMATIC MUSIC FADES UP )</i>

904
01:15:03,966 --> 01:15:07,235
<i>ANNA (V.O.): It's not</i>
<i>your fault, John.</i>

905
01:15:10,339 --> 01:15:13,174
<i>ROCKFORD (ON TV): This</i>
<i>person... they lied</i>
<i>about everything.</i>

906
01:15:13,176 --> 01:15:16,944
<i>But just because the lies are</i>
<i>shocking and they attract a</i>
<i>lot of attention...</i>

907
01:15:16,946 --> 01:15:19,647
it doesn't necessarily
make them true.

908
01:15:19,649 --> 01:15:22,016
It was very important
for us to...

909
01:15:22,018 --> 01:15:24,619
<i>to check the facts and to</i>
<i>question the facts...</i>

910
01:15:24,621 --> 01:15:26,954
until it was evident that
I was innocent.

911
01:15:26,956 --> 01:15:30,992
<i>And once we've proven my</i>
<i>innocence, we went back</i>
<i>to that proof...</i>

912
01:15:30,994 --> 01:15:34,428
<i>over and over again, and looked</i>
<i>at it with a fresh set of eyes.</i>

913
01:15:34,430 --> 01:15:38,799
<i>Because only then, were we able</i>
<i>to actually see the truth.</i>

914
01:15:38,801 --> 01:15:41,302
<i>Are there any questions?</i>

915
01:15:41,304 --> 01:15:43,070
REPORTER (O.S.): How does it
feel to be designated?

916
01:15:43,072 --> 01:15:44,839
<i>ROCKWELL (O.S.): That's a</i>
<i>good question...</i>

917
01:15:44,841 --> 01:15:46,374
<i>and I just want to thank my</i>
<i>constituency...</i>

918
01:15:46,376 --> 01:15:49,277
( SOFT MUSIC PLAYING )

919
01:16:22,778 --> 01:16:26,280
<i>( DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING )</i>

920
01:17:03,885 --> 01:17:07,054
ANNA (V.O.): I just
downloaded it.

921
01:17:07,056 --> 01:17:09,824
Aren't they great? Better than
what you had before.

922
01:17:22,671 --> 01:17:26,073
<i>( DRAMATIC MUSIC FADES UP )</i>

923
01:17:43,525 --> 01:17:46,927
( PHONE RINGING )

924
01:17:46,929 --> 01:17:49,363
Hello?
<i>ANNA (ON PHONE):</i>
<i>Can you come over?</i>

925
01:17:49,365 --> 01:17:50,564
I need to see you, John.

926
01:17:50,566 --> 01:17:51,732
Anna, look, I need to talk to--

927
01:17:51,734 --> 01:17:53,668
Before it's too late!

928
01:17:53,670 --> 01:17:55,670
<i>Something terrible has</i>
<i>happened and I need to...</i>

929
01:17:55,672 --> 01:18:00,041
What? Hello?

930
01:18:00,043 --> 01:18:02,343
<i>( BUSY SIGNAL )</i>
Hello?

931
01:18:02,345 --> 01:18:06,213
( PHONE RINGS )

932
01:18:06,215 --> 01:18:08,382
<i>MICHELLE (ON PHONE): You have</i>
<i>reached the Greene's residence.</i>

933
01:18:08,384 --> 01:18:11,519
<i>Please leave a message and</i>
<i>we'll get back to you as</i>
<i>soon as we can.</i>

934
01:18:11,521 --> 01:18:13,821
( BEEPS )

935
01:18:17,392 --> 01:18:20,161
<i>( DRAMATIC MUSIC CONTINUES )</i>

936
01:18:52,260 --> 01:18:53,861
( DISTANT DOOR CLOSING )

937
01:18:53,863 --> 01:18:56,964
( STEPS APPROACHING ) Hello?

938
01:19:34,836 --> 01:19:37,605
Anna?
<i>ANNA (O.S.):</i>
<i>John.</i>

939
01:20:15,944 --> 01:20:19,446
( DOOR LOCK CLICKS )

940
01:20:19,448 --> 01:20:23,317
<i>( DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING )</i>

941
01:20:23,319 --> 01:20:25,419
Hey!

942
01:20:25,421 --> 01:20:27,354
Open the door!

943
01:20:27,356 --> 01:20:31,559
<i>ANNA (O.S.): John, there's</i>
<i>someone in our house!</i>

944
01:20:35,597 --> 01:20:37,598
( ANNA SCREAMS )

945
01:20:39,000 --> 01:20:42,203
<i>( BUSY SIGNAL )</i>
Shit!

946
01:20:42,205 --> 01:20:45,606
Mom? Mom?

947
01:20:45,608 --> 01:20:46,907
Hello?

948
01:20:46,909 --> 01:20:48,042
<i>OPERATOR (ON PHONE):</i>
<i>Wh-- emergency--</i>

949
01:20:48,044 --> 01:20:49,176
Hello, can you hear me?

950
01:20:49,178 --> 01:20:51,011
( OPERATOR VOICE GARBLED )

951
01:20:53,582 --> 01:20:55,082
Shit.

952
01:20:55,084 --> 01:20:56,417
ANNA (ON MONITOR): I
don't want to die!

953
